text.tspan: a report from Oxfam found that line workers at Tyson Foods,
Perdue Farms, Pilgrim's Pride, and Sanderson Farms were denied breaks.
In fact, they went so long without breaks that some employees were
forced to wear diapers.
To make matters worse, slaughterhouse violence not only subjects
countless workers to serious psychological trauma
but also makes its way into the communities they are part of.
Source:
https://mercyforanimals.org/slaughterhouse-workers-have-ptsd-from-killing
The people who allow other people to develop
PTSD will have no remorse for the animals
they’re killing
Capitalism is the biggest obstacle in the
way of cruely-free consumption.
The Animal Liberation Movement and the
proletariat have one common enemy.
Even if you don’t agree that animal liberation
is an extension of th class struggle, you must
understand that solidarity and cooperation
is in our best interests.
Veganism without anticapitalism is
utterly worthless.
